    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Key Concepts"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "**Sample space**: Set of all possible outcomes.",
        "**Event**: Subset of sample space.",
        "$P(E) = |E|/|S|$ for equally likely outcomes.",
        "$P(\\bar{E}) = 1 - P(E)$ (complement rule).",
        "**Conditional probability**: $P(E | F) = P(E \\cap F)/P(F)$.",
        "**Independence**: $P(E \\cap F) = P(E) \\cdot P(F)$.",
        "**Bayes' theorem**: $P(E | F) = P(F | E) P(E) / P(F)$.",
        "**Random variable**: Function from outcomes to numbers.",
        "**Expected value**: $E[X] = \\sum_x x \\cdot P(X = x)$.",
        "**Variance**: $\\text{Var}(X) = E[X^2] - (E[X])^2$."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Important Distributions"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "headers": [
